QGIS and ArcGIS are the two most widely used GIS (Geographic Information System) platforms, but they differ a lot in philosophy, cost, ecosystem, and typical use cases.
As QGIS is the free one, that is the one we will use :
QGIS (Quantum Geographic Information System) is a free, open-source GIS software used to create, edit, analyze, and visualize geographic (spatial) data.
